abstract: Its move to hire HTC engineers is intended to improve competition with Apple and Samsung. But the tech giant’s previous foray into handset making did not go so well.
snippet: Its move to hire HTC engineers is intended to improve competition with Apple and Samsung. But the tech giant’s previous foray into handset making did not go so well.
lead_paragraph: Google once owned a phone maker. It didn’t work out. Now it’s trying a different approach.

abstract: In a symbolic passing of the guard, Mr. Clinton will be the first speaker Wednesday at the Bloomberg Global Business Forum.
snippet: In a symbolic passing of the guard, Mr. Clinton will be the first speaker Wednesday at the Bloomberg Global Business Forum.
lead_paragraph: For more than a decade, the Clinton Global Initiative was the star-studded marquee attraction during the annual meeting of the United Nations General Assembly, a place where heads of state, celebrities, billionaire philanthropists and business people mingled, made deals and gave away millions, sometimes billions, of dollars.

abstract: The bankruptcy filing by Toys “R” Us shows just how much pain store operators are feeling — and highlighted that more suffering is in store.
snippet: The bankruptcy filing by Toys “R” Us shows just how much pain store operators are feeling — and highlighted that more suffering is in store.
lead_paragraph: If you’re a retailer and you’re not Amazon or Walmart, life can be very hard. The bankruptcy filing by Toys “R” Us on Monday is just the latest example.

abstract: Facebook, Google and other technology titans are encountering more resistance to their empire-building, both abroad and at home.
snippet: Facebook, Google and other technology titans are encountering more resistance to their empire-building, both abroad and at home.
lead_paragraph: For a long time, American technology giants have received a chilly reception from skeptical audiences in Europe, including from government regulators, while at home, companies like Google, Facebook and Amazon have been largely lauded for their innovation and their astonishing growth.

abstract: Officials in Manatee County, Fla., drew criticism for asking a local lifeguard unskilled at sign language to interpret crucial evacuation orders.
snippet: Officials in Manatee County, Fla., drew criticism for asking a local lifeguard unskilled at sign language to interpret crucial evacuation orders.
lead_paragraph: As Hurricane Irma charged toward Florida, officials in a county on the state’s west coast held a news conference to inform residents of mandatory evacuation orders for those most at risk.

headline_print_headline: Who Will Inherit the Throne at Vanity Fair?
byline_original: By Michael M. Grynbaum and Sydney Ember

abstract: If New York has turned inward and become obsessed with its screens, is Bill de Blasio, on his way to a second term, the mayor the city deserves?
snippet: If New York has turned inward and become obsessed with its screens, is Bill de Blasio, on his way to a second term, the mayor the city deserves?
lead_paragraph: It seemed perhaps all too appropriate that on the day after Bill de Blasio, master of somnolent arrogance, effectively won a second term as the mayor of New York City, came a report that a former product manager at Google and his partner had started a company called Bodega, meant to rid cities of actual bodegas.

abstract: Nestlé’s deal for a majority stake in Blue Bottle Coffee is in part an effort to reach coffee-loving millennials. Other food giants may be hunting similar targets.
snippet: Nestlé’s deal for a majority stake in Blue Bottle Coffee is in part an effort to reach coffee-loving millennials. Other food giants may be hunting similar targets.
lead_paragraph: Nestlé built its coffee kingdom on Nescafé and Nespresso pods. But the Swiss food giant is aiming higher with its newest deal: buying a majority stake in Blue Bottle Coffee, part of the vanguard of so-called third wave coffee. (Disclaimer: one of us drank a lot of Blue Bottle when living in San Francisco.)

abstract: The mayor may well coast to a second term in November, but just one day after a decisive primary victory, the governor needled him by praising his predecessor.
snippet: The mayor may well coast to a second term in November, but just one day after a decisive primary victory, the governor needled him by praising his predecessor.
lead_paragraph: It was the morning after a resounding primary victory for Mayor Bill de Blasio, the kind that political mandates are made of, and as luck would have it, the mayor of New York had a tailor-made moment to bask in the glow of electoral success.
